&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 SLT 0.8 WTE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Deaf Team, Special Schools Service in Haringey is looking for a skilled and innovative speech and language therapist with experience in working with Deaf children and young people from 5 to 18 years old, and keen to further develop specialist skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with pupils at Blanche Nevile School for the Deaf which is in partnership with a primary and secondary mainstream school (Highgate and Fortismere). You will be one of 4 SLT’s delivering high quality and innovative therapy and teaching approaches to pupils with a primary communication need due to deafness, as well as those who have significant communication needs additional to their deafness. You will require a minimum of 2 years experience as an SLT and have Level 2 BSL.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will organise and manage your own caseload and continue to build and maintain strong relationships with Blanche Nevile School. You will receive regular supervision from the Clinical Lead therapist in Deafness and will have opportunities to work closely with colleagues both senior and junior within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date for applications is 22.11.20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Karin Schamroth, Clinical Lead SLT for Deafness on 07989 852 980 / karin.schamroth@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKarin SchamrothJob titleLead Specialist Speech &amp; Language Therapist in DeafnessEmail addresskarin.schamroth@nhs.netTelephone number07989 852 980&lt;/p&gt;
